                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7597: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-01T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1926—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 1—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>366. My 360, August 30, 5 p.m. Following from American consul general at Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Concessions here overcrowded with refugees. Frightened Chinese from the
                            native city still coming in, creating great concern and resulting in
                            much confusion. They are much alarmed, not at the prospect apparently of
                            the Southern troops arriving but of looting by Northern troops. In case
                            of trouble in the concession, foreign volunteer forces and naval units
                            will be utilized, in cooperation with the Chinese authorities, in
                            protecting life and property. Chinese authorities have made such a
                            request of the foreign consuls. Wu is known to be in desperate straits
                            across the river and this is having an unfavorable reaction here.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
